HEADWORD: Impertransible
<hw>Im`per*tran"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>pertransire</ets> to go through. See
<er>Per-</er> and <er>Transient</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being
passed through.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperturbability</ent>⟦br⟧
